Tech executive with decades of experience including general management of all size organizations, sales, operations, staffing methods and internet platform strategy.

Grace Terrell Greensboro/Winston-Salem, North Carolina Area Hospital & Health Care President/CEO Cornerstone Health Care Summary
Dr. Grace Terrell is a national and local leader in health care delivery system reform. She travels across the country working with organizations and speaking to groups about how to improve population health for all patients through patient care model redesign, clinical and information integration, and value-based compensation. In 2013, Dr. Terrell paved the way for the launching of CHESS, a company dedicated to helping health systems and other medical groups make the transition to value-based medicine.

For over 15 years, Dr. Terrell served as the President and CEO of Cornerstone Health Care, a physician-owned and led multi-disciplinary practice of more than 330 physicians and mid-level health professionals. Cornerstone is ranked one of the highest quality ACOs in the nation and received the 2015 AMGA Acclaim Award ™ for their efforts at working to be a high performing health system including transforming to value-based contracts based on cost-effectiveness and quality.

Dr. Terrell currently serves on the U.S. Department of Health and Human Services’ Physician-Focused Payment Model Technical Advisory Committee (PTAC), the Board of Directors of the American Medical Group Association, the American Medical Association’s Integrated Physician section, and the Oliver Wyman Health Innovation Center’s Leadership Alliance in addition to practice internal medicine at Cornerstone Internal Medicine at Westchester. Jill McDonough Sartell, Minnesota Insurance Manager, Employee Benefits Operations at Marsh & McLennan Agency - Upper Midwest Summary
My experience includes nearly 15 years of account management in the employee benefits field. My most recent experience involved managing a book of key accounts that exceeded $1,000,000. These accounts were a broad mix of fully-insured and self-insured clients, and my experience involved all aspects of plan administration.

The service that I provided included consulting in all lines of employee benefits coverage; medical, dental, life, disability and voluntary benefits. In addition to presenting renewal and alternative plan designs, I managed the marketing process, negotiating on behalf of the client with multiple local and national medical and ancillary insurance carriers. This process included securing sold coverage, implementation and employee enrollment. On a quarterly basis, I met with clients to review claims and experience utilization and how this utilization impacted the current budget and projected renewal of the plan. I worked closely with our internal underwriting team to evaluate trends in utilization and methods of cost containment for areas of concern.

The enrollment and communication of these benefits to employees was conducted via multiple avenues, including creating written memos, employee benefit guides, webinars, online videos and in-person meetings. Beyond the scope of employee communication, I was also a day-to-day liaison for both the employer and employee in regards to benefits, claims, billing and enrollment questions and concerns.

Other areas of my role involved consulting clients in regards to ACA compliance, the employer-shared responsibility mandate and communication of the individual mandate to employees. Due to the ever-changing environment of the current industry, I was also very involved in consulting about technology solutions and wellness initiatives.

I currently hold a life/health license in the state of Minnesota, and am in the process of obtaining my CEBS designation, with the first two courses completed. Education
Argosy University Twin Cities
